description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals Trust are seeking to recruit to a Service Manager for Bereavement &amp; Medical Examiner Officer Services, a new and developing service the role will be central in the implementation and integration of this new service within the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will provide leadership and management to staff within the Bereavement and Medical Examiner Office, alongside establishing and sustaining an effective and responsive service. This is an exciting opportunity and will work in collaboration with the Medical Examiner/Examiners in their role in scrutinising the circumstances and cause of death for all patients within the Trust with a particular focus on the highly complex deaths, providing assistance and advice as required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate/s would require excellent interpersonal and communication skills and demonstrate a high level of tact and diplomacy due to the sensitive nature of the role. This is an exciting opportunity to make a difference for both patients and their families/carers and staff within the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Anne-Marie Walsh, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Trust Risk Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;0113 2064934&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
